text:
Be cautious of possible deceptive practices at the cai fan stall (#S02) by Unicuz.

I bought 狮子头 ($2) from the stall, but the female server claimed it contained fish and charged $3. Upon returning home, I found no fish in it. I went back to the stall for clarification.

The female server returned the extra $1 without an apology, insisting it wasn’t her fault and blaming a mix-up by someone else. Her dismissive attitude made it unclear whether it was a genuine mistake or intentional deception.

TL;DR: The cai fan stall provided incorrect information and overcharged for food. Beware of potential dishonest behavior.
小炒王is very good. Reasonable prices and cheerful service. The pork rib king was tasty. The prawn paste chicken was good too. Curry fishhead was generous.

This kopitiam is quite a nice place to chill as it  is quite spacious and breezy. Food choices are diverse but the quality is rather substandard. I have tried the Indian food stall and the fried Hokkien prawn mee and both were mediocre.

Nice place to eat at the corner of the road of 115b commonwealth. Nasi lemak is nice and the sambal is spicy! I love it! The mee siam is also nice. It’s affordable at only $4.
Menu:
- Nasi lemak
- Mee Siam
- Mee Rebus
- Mee Soto
- Lontong
- Porridge
- Chicken Cutlet Rice
- Epok Kentang/Sardine
- Hot Dog Roll (my fav)
- etc

Drink stall aunty has no common sense. After I order “drinking water” and she doesn’t understand until I need to repeat 2-3 times for just a bottle of water and end up she poured the water from JUG!!!  I was so speechless and paid 1$ for stupid water.
